# Astro images

Canonical examples: `@src/components/Hero.astro` (LCP), `@src/components/About.astro` / `@src/components/Portfolio.astro` (lazy).

## Where files live

- Optimizable photos/content images: import from `src/assets/images/` and use `Picture` from `astro:assets`.
- Favicons, OG image, decorative SVGs: may stay in `public/`.
- Keep `sharp` installed for the default image service.

## Picture defaults

- Use `formats={['avif', 'webp']}`, explicit `width` / `height`, and `layout="constrained"`.
- `alt` is required. Decorative icons: `alt=""` plus `aria-hidden="true"`.

## Loading strategy

- LCP / above-the-fold: `loading="eager"` + `fetchpriority="high"` + `decoding="async"`
- Below-fold: `loading="lazy"` + `decoding="async"` — never eager-load gallery/about/portfolio images
- Do **not** use Astro's `priority` prop here — it sets `decoding="sync"`, which diverges from this site's Hero pattern.

```astro
<!-- ❌ BAD: lazy LCP hero, or raw public/ photo without Picture -->
<img src="/img/hero.png" alt="…" />

<!-- ✅ GOOD: LCP -->
<Picture
  src={hero}
  formats={['avif', 'webp']}
  alt="…"
  width={500}
  height={792}
  layout="constrained"
  loading="eager"
  fetchpriority="high"
  decoding="async"
/>

<!-- ✅ GOOD: below-fold -->
<Picture … loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
```
